# Docker (pass as env vars):
# docker run -e SUPABASE_URL="https://..." -e SUPABASE_KEY="abc..." myapp

# =====================================================
# WHEN DEPLOYING TO PRODUCTION
# =====================================================

# 1. Use different keys for different environments
#    - Keep "anon" key for frontend/Colab (read-safe)
#    - Use API key for backend (has write access)

# 2. Enable Row Level Security (RLS) in Supabase
#    - Look in your database: Settings → RLS
#    - Make sure policies are enabled

# 3. Keep backups of important config
#    - Screenshot your Supabase settings
#    - Save API keys in password manager
#    - Keep recovery codes safe

# 4. Monitor usage
#    - Supabase: Settings → Usage
#    - HuggingFace: Space settings → Logs
#    - Vercel: Deployments → Function logs

# 5. Scale thoughtfully
#    - Start with free tier
#    - Monitor metrics
#    - Upgrade when needed (not costly)

# =====================================================
# QUESTIONS?
